commit.message:
Windows: Fix caching for non-ASCII profile paths; fix build failure with Qt 6.

If path for cache directory contained non-ASCII characters then the
cache was not being created.  This could happen in case user name
contained such characters or a windows user profile related environment
variable pointed to such path.

Build on Windows with Qt 6 was failing because UNICODE preprocessor
constant is set in such scenario and it caused that Unicode versions
of some windows functions were build instead of ANSI.  The interfacing
code was not compatible with Unicode versions of windows functions.
This was fixed by using Unicode version only and adapting the interfacing
code.

Fix undefined symbols error caused by broken Qt MOs compilation.

When versionless support is not used now, the qt_wrap_cpp does not work because
it has to be either qt5_wrap_cpp or qt6_wrap_cpp.  Since qt_wrap_cpp is anyway
deprecated, switch to AUTOMOC.
Explicitly turn off Qt versionless targets and functions.

Merge pull request #7 from robert-scheck/v1.0-older-qt5

Fix building using Qt < 5.15.

commit.message:
Fix building using Qt < 5.15

Building using Qt 5.9.7 (e.g. RHEL/CentOS 7) fails like this:

CMake Error at CMakeLists.txt:103 (add_library):
  Target "ampache_browser" links to target "Qt::Core" but the target was not
  found.  Perhaps a find_package() call is missing for an IMPORTED target, or
  an ALIAS target is missing?
CMake Error at CMakeLists.txt:103 (add_library):
  Target "ampache_browser" links to target "Qt::Widgets" but the target was
  not found.  Perhaps a find_package() call is missing for an IMPORTED
  target, or an ALIAS target is missing?
CMake Error at CMakeLists.txt:103 (add_library):
  Target "ampache_browser" links to target "Qt::Concurrent" but the target
  was not found.  Perhaps a find_package() call is missing for an IMPORTED
  target, or an ALIAS target is missing?

Patch inspired by https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/cmake-qt5-and-qt6-compatibility.html#supporting-older-qt-5-versions

Fix sorting of tracks on albums with multiple disks.

Ampache started to serve multiple disk albums as one album instead of
each disk separately.  Ampache Browser orders tracks by track number.
This lead to wrong ordering if tracks were numbered on each disk from
"1".  The track order in such case was:

1. track 1 (from disk 1)
2. track 1 (from disk 2)
...

After the fix the order is correct:

1. track 1 (from disk 1)
2. track 2 (from disk 1)
...

Required API version was increased to 440001.  Older APIs does not contain
disk number.

Cache version changed and the cache version change is now handled
correctly.

Substract myNumberOfUnavailableEntries in maxCount().

maxCount() now returns number of items as returned by data provider minus
number of unavailable items.  This gracefully handles situation when
Ampache returns higher item count than really available.

The concrete issue was that Ampache returns higher number of albums than
really available and then loading never finished because repository was
still waiting for seemingly missing arts to be loaded.
Do not autodetect Qt version during build.
Fix One Definition Rule violation (-Wodr) when building with -flto.
Increase version number and update NEWS.

Use QImage instead of QPixmap in asynchronous loading of album arts.

Using QPixmap (or QPixmapCache) concurrently causes random crashes
during album arts loading.
